01:48:49,600 --> 01:48:56,560
in the bottom and pushed it under the water. 
Soon it went down to the bottom of the sea.

970
01:48:58,640 --> 01:49:04,160
Rafael was happy. The soldier and his 
boat were at the bottom of the sea.  

971
01:49:05,600 --> 01:49:11,840
Nobody knew what happened to him. He 
went back to the village and into the  

972
01:49:11,840 --> 01:49:17,120
house to have an early breakfast. 
Suddenly he was very hungry.
 
 
 

973
01:49:22,880 --> 01:49:23,760
CHAPTER FIFTEEN

974
01:49:25,040 --> 01:49:27,840
The Truth, at Last

975
01:49:30,160 --> 01:49:37,280
A little later (Rafael told me), he and 
his mother heard the shouting and screaming  

976
01:49:37,280 --> 01:49:43,440
from Rodrigo's house. They soon learned that 
Anita was nowhere in the house or the village.  

977
01:49:44,640 --> 01:49:50,480
Rafael smiled to himself. Perhaps Anita was 
still waiting somewhere for her soldier.  

978
01:49:51,840 --> 01:49:55,840
'She can wait forever. She'll 
never see him again,' he thought.

979
01:49:57,920 --> 01:50:05,360
'I'll sail along the coast and look for her,' he 
told his mother. In fact, he wanted to go to a  

980
01:50:05,360 --> 01:50:09,840
quiet place to wash his boat again. There 
was still some dark blood in the bottom.

981
01:50:12,000 --> 01:50:14,080
He went back to the place in the rocks. 

982
01:50:15,600 --> 01:50:20,720
It was calm and quiet there. The soldier's 
boat was at the bottom of the sea.  

983
01:50:22,480 --> 01:50:25,520
Rafael took some water from 
the sea to wash his boat.  

984
01:50:27,120 --> 01:50:34,960
A small shark swam slowly under it. Almost without 
thinking, Rafael picked up his fishing spear.  

985
01:50:36,160 --> 01:50:43,680
He hit the shark hard through the back of the 
head. Its blood came out into the clear water. A  

986
01:50:43,680 --> 01:50:50,480
few other sharks, bigger ones, smelt the blood and 
came fast through the water. They began to bite at  

987
01:50:50,480 --> 01:50:56,720
the dying fish with their great, sharp teeth. They 
fought, biting great pieces off the dead shark.

988
01:50:58,400 --> 01:51:02,320
Rafael decided to catch one or 
two and cut them up in his boat.  

989
01:51:03,520 --> 01:51:06,240
He wanted their blood to be 
in the boat with the donkey's.

990
01:51:07,920 --> 01:51:11,840
A white shark about three metres 
long was pulling at the dead one.  

991
01:51:12,960 --> 01:51:18,240
If lay in the water next to the boat, 
not moving. Rafael killed it with his  

992
01:51:18,240 --> 01:51:24,160
spear and put a line round its head. Then 
he pulled it into the bottom of the boat.

993
01:51:26,240 --> 01:51:30,240
Rafael took his knife and cut 
the shark open from neck to tail.  

994
01:51:31,760 --> 01:51:37,760
Pieces of meat, fish and hair from its Stomach 
fell out into the bottom of the boat. There  

995
01:51:37,760 --> 01:51:43,200
was a large piece of donkey skin with its 
grey hair. Rafael moved it with his knife.

996
01:51:45,440 --> 01:51:48,160
In that second, the world stopped.  

997
01:51:49,600 --> 01:51:55,200
Rafael's blood seemed to freeze inside 
him. The sky went dark. He couldn't move.

998
01:51:57,360 --> 01:52:02,800
In the pile of meat and fish in the 
bottom of the boat there was a hand.

999
01:52:04,000 --> 01:52:11,520
A complete hand, white and clean. 
It was cut off at the wrist with one  

1000
01:52:11,520 --> 01:52:20,880
clean bite. It was a small hand, with small, 
pretty fingers. The fingernails were long and  

1001
01:52:20,880 --> 01:52:25,200
pink. They weren't bitten or 
dirty or broken by housework.

1002
01:52:27,200 --> 01:52:34,880
And on the middle finger of the hand was a 
gold ring, a ring in the shape of a golden fish

1003
01:52:37,600 --> 01:52:48,000
Rafael gave one great scream. He held his head 
in his hands. He knew now where Anita was.  

1004
01:52:49,840 --> 01:52:54,640
The night before, when the engine of 
the soldier's boat stopped working,  

1005
01:52:55,840 --> 01:53:02,080
she was there in the boat with him. Then he 
went into the water to look at the engine.  

1006
01:53:03,120 --> 01:53:08,880
She stayed in the boat. She saw him, when 
the sharks killed him in the dark water.  

1007
01:53:09,520 --> 01:53:16,880
Perhaps she tried to pull him into the boat. 
But then she too fell into the blood-red water.  

1008
01:53:17,600 --> 01:53:23,760
And there she spent the last terrible seconds 
of her life with her true prince, the soldier.

1009
01:53:25,680 --> 01:53:31,520
Rafael knew he couldn't continue living. 
He couldn't live with this terrible secret.  

1010
01:53:32,720 --> 01:53:39,840
He stood up in the boat and called Anita's 
name. Then he threw himself into the sea.  

1011
01:53:40,560 --> 01:53:46,560
He lay in the water, face down. He waited 
for the sharp teeth in the mouths of the  

1012
01:53:46,560 --> 01:53:55,680
sharks to pull him down to his death. But they 
didn't. He felt them in the water all round him.  

1013
01:53:56,880 --> 01:54:02,240
Sometimes he felt them push against 
him. But they didn't hurt him.

1014
01:54:03,680 --> 01:54:12,640
Then Rafael understood. God didn't want him 
to die this way. An easy death. A quick death.  

1015
01:54:13,440 --> 01:54:21,840
Too quick and easy for a murderer. He was 
terribly afraid. He tried to kill himself.  

1016
01:54:22,400 --> 01:54:27,120
He held his face under the water 
and tried to die. But he couldn't.

1017
01:54:29,760 --> 01:54:32,160
At last he climbed back into the boat.  

1018
01:54:33,760 --> 01:54:39,040
He sat like a dead man and looked at 
the little hand with the gold ring.  

1019
01:54:41,280 --> 01:54:47,600
After a long time he took the ring carefully 
from her finger. He took a piece of fishing  

1020
01:54:47,600 --> 01:54:57,680
line and tied the ring round his neck. He had 
his ring again. He had it from Anita's own hand.  

1021
01:54:59,840 --> 01:55:07,520
'I'll keep it with me forever,' he thought. 
'Then I will never forget my terrible crime.'

1022
01:55:09,840 --> 01:55:12,320
He threw the dead shark back into the sea.

1023
01:55:14,560 --> 01:55:19,280
Then, last of all, he took the cold white hand.  

1024
01:55:21,200 --> 01:55:27,760
He held it in his own hand for the last time. 
Then he put it carefully into the water.

1025
01:55:30,480 --> 01:55:34,720
Then he lay down in the bottom of the 
boat holding the ring at his neck.  

1026
01:55:36,160 --> 01:55:45,840
And he looked at the bright sky and talked 
to Anita. And they laughed and laughed...

1027
01:55:46,920 --> 01:55:47,920
***

1028
01:55:47,920 --> 01:55:54,880
I took Rafael's body back to his village. He 
lies in the ground near that place in the rocks.  

1029
01:55:55,600 --> 01:56:03,360
The secret place where he and Anita spent many 
happy hours. I put the gold ring round his neck.  

1030
01:56:04,560 --> 01:56:10,000
The ring that he took from Anita's dead 
hand. It will stay with him forever.

1031
01:56:12,640 --> 01:56:18,880
Nobody in the village knows what he 
did. Not Rodrigo, not my uncle or Rosa.  

1032
01:56:20,640 --> 01:56:27,840
They still believe that Anita and the 
soldier are living somewhere far away.

1033
01:56:28,800 --> 01:56:39,680
I can see no reason to tell 
them anything different.
 
 
 
 

1034
01:56:39,680 --> 01:56:40,242
- THE END -

